 Milan | year = 1982 | title = The Yugoslav Navy 1918–1941 | journal = Warship International | volume = | issue = 4 | pages = 342–361 | issn = 0043-0374 | publisher = International Naval Research Organisation | location = Toledo, Ohio | ref = harv }} {{refend}} {{Yugoslav 250t-class torpedo boats}} {{DEFAULTSORT:T5}} [[Category:Ships built in Fiume]] [[Category:Torpedo boats of the Austro-Hungarian Navy]] [[Category:World War I torpedo boats of Austria-Hungary]] [[Category:Ships of the Royal Yugoslav Navy]] [[Category:Naval ships of Yugoslavia captured by Italy during World War II]] [[Category:1915 ships]] [[Category:Torpedo boats of the Royal Yugoslav Navy]] [[Category:Ships of the Yugoslav Navy]]

